      <body>
         <listPlace>
            <place type="church dabr" subtype="institution">
               <placeName>Dabri Dabra Zakāryās Qǝddus Giyorgis</placeName>
               <placeName type="alt">Dabri Qǝddus Giyorgis</placeName>
               <country ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3010Ethiop">ʾItyoṗyā</country>
               <region notBefore="1991" type="RegionalState" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5932Tegray">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy</region>
               
               <settlement type="warada" from="2012-11-16" to="2012-12-04" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3293GantaA">Gāntā ʾAfašum</settlement>  
               <settlement type="tabiya" from="2012-11-16" to="2012-12-04" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7181Gwahgot">Gwāḥgot</settlement>
               
               <settlement from="2012-11-16" to="2012-12-04" type="qushat" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7252Dabri">Dabri</settlement>
               
               <location>
                  <geo>14.141549 39.492582</geo>
                  <height unit="m">2587.96</height>
               </location>
               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1200" notAfter="1300">1200-1300</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Local tradition claims that the church was founded in the time of King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4327GabraMa">Gabra Masqal</persName>, the tābot was brought by King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3729ellaAm">ʾAlʿāmedā</persName>.</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Dabr. Aksumite remains have been found in the vicinity. 
                     The recent church of <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh#n3MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</persName> was built in the time of ; before,  (?).
The church of St. <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">George</persName> stands on the rock and is hardly accessible. 
                     The structures visible in the rock under the church of George (?) are said to have been a church dedicated to <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3249Cyriacus">Qirqos</persName> (now deserted and inaccessible). 
                     In the valley, there is an associated church dedicated to <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh#n3MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</persName>, built in <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5226haylase">King Ḫāyla Śǝllāse</persName>'s time (<date>1930-1950</date>?; but it was founded by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6841MasasaW">
                        <roleName type="title">grāzmāč</roleName> Mašašā</persName>).  
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">
                     <figure>
                        <graphic url="Sites/DQG.tif">
                           <desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</desc>
                        </graphic>
                     </figure>10 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg001">DQG-001</ref> “Miracles of Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg002">DQG-002</ref> “Vita of Mar Giyorgis”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg003">DQG-003</ref> “Compilation of gospel's texts”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg004">DQG-004</ref> “Miracles of Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg005">DQG-005</ref> “Vita of Giyorgis; Miracles of Giyorgis; Supplication prayer; Image of Giyorgis”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg006">DQG-006</ref> “Psalter”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg007">DQG-007</ref> “Harp of Praise”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg008">DQG-008</ref> “Four Gospels”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg009">DQG-009</ref> “Book of the Baptismal Ritual”; <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdqg010">DQG-010</ref> “Praise of Marry”.</ab>
      
                  <ab type="tabot">
                     <measure quantity="3"/>Tābots of 2 of <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">George</persName> (in the upper church) and 1 <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh#n3MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</persName> (below). 
                     The tābot of <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3249Cyriacus">Qirqos</persName> is not there any more (reportedly stolen). The old dedication might be reflected in the name of the church, Dabra Zakāryās (<persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10692Zechari">Prophet Zechariah</persName>?).</ab>
               </note>
            </place>
